01:11:09.000 --> 01:11:18.000
And one woman told me that every time she went down to no this was all African American folk black folk if one wants to use that term.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:35.000
Every time I go down to the courthouse the clerk the city clerk would just be so insulting and I was trying to tell her that they would the people who would test the well water would test all the white folks water but would not test the water in my well.

01:11:35.000 --> 01:11:45.000
And I remember the second day she again was so energized and just stirred about the fact that they would test everybody's well water but the water for black folk.

01:11:45.000 --> 01:11:52.000
And the third day she's ready to tell me that same story again and I said well why aren't you the city clerk?

01:11:52.000 --> 01:12:09.000
And I love telling that story because it really makes the point of how there was this there's no such thing as an audible silence but the other ways to describe the energy in the room at that moment.

01:12:09.000 --> 01:12:29.000
And the transformation obviously that was happening with not only her but because that's why they were there to decide that they were not going to be victims anymore but incident that that's I'm using a part of that language in the title of the book that I'm doing.

01:12:29.000 --> 01:12:46.000
And Dr. King came to close out one of the workshops for me I called him and said would you please come the if your backs not bent the movement from victim to victory.

01:12:46.000 --> 01:13:15.000
